com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations.sequence

Class OligoSequenceDocument

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.AbstractPluginDocument
      • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations.sequence.DefaultSequenceDocument
        • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations.sequence.DefaultNucleotideSequence
          • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations.sequence.OligoSequenceDocument
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PluginDocument, Renamable, EditableSequenceDocument, NucleotideSequenceDocument, SequenceDocument, SequenceDocumentWithEditableAnnotations, XMLSerializable, XMLSerializable.OldVersionCompatible, SequenceTrack.Manager.Provider, SequenceGapInformation.Provider

    public class OligoSequenceDocument
extends DefaultNucleotideSequence
    A sequence document which represents an olgionucleotide such as a Primer or DNA probe. Special properties include displayable fields for common oligo stats such as melting point and GC content as well as a special text view which displays the oligo properties. The collection of all OligoSequenceDocuments in a user's database makes up their "primer database" which is used when testing primers.

    The sequence for the class consists of two parts: a binding region and potentially an extension. The binding region (which can be retrieved using getBindingInterval() and getBindingSequence()) is the part of the sequence which must match a target sequence for binding to occur. The extension (which is the remainder of DefaultSequenceDocument.getSequenceString()) is made optional additional bases (eg. a restriction site) which will be introduced to the end of the PCR product. An extension is optional.

      • SOURCE_QUALIFIER_NAME

        public static final String SOURCE_QUALIFIER_NAME
        Deprecated. from 7.0.0, this field is not added to new primer annotations
        Name to use for SequenceAnnotationQualifiers to provide a reference back to the original OligoSequenceDocument from which an annotation was created.

        If an OligoSequenceDocument with an extension has had its binding region annotated onto another sequence then the extension is not visible. However the annotation should still hold a reference to the original OligoSequenceDocument by storing a qualifier that uses this name and has a value of the URN of the source document. This qualifier is hidden from the Geneious user interface. This, for example, is done by the bundled Primer and Probe Design Plugin when doing Test Primers.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXTENSION_QUALIFIER_NAME

        public static final String EXTENSION_QUALIFIER_NAME
        Name to use for SequenceAnnotationQualifiers that specify any primer extension sequence in addition to the primer binding region.

        An OligoSequenceDocument may have an extension in addition to the binding sequence. If the binding region is annotated onto a sequence then the extension will appear as a qualifier of the binding annotation.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • OligoSequenceDocument

        public OligoSequenceDocument(NucleotideSequenceDocument sequenceDocument)
        Create an OligoSequenceDocument from an existing SequenceDocument. If this is being used to replace an existing sequence in the database then the caller should copy any notes across from the AnnotatedPluginDocument. This constructor copies all displayable fields and values from the source SequenceDocument.

        Primer characteristics such as TM and GC% are not added in this class, they must be added separately as an annotation by the core Primer plugin. Primer characteristics will be picked up from a primer_bind annotation if there is one and only one that covers the sequence entirely. If such an annotation exists and the sequence qualifier for the annotation differs from the source sequence itself, then the sequence in the qualifier will be used for the sequence of this document.

        Parameters:
        sequenceDocument - the sequence document to copy data from

      • setSequenceAndAnnotations

        public void setSequenceAndAnnotations(CharSequence sequence,
                             List<SequenceAnnotation> annotations)
        Description copied from interface: EditableSequenceDocument
        Sets the sequence and annotations of this document. This does not replace annotations on SequenceTracks

        If this changes the length of the sequence, this is only allowed if this document is not a NucleotideGraphSequence (because the graph site positions and qualities would have to be updated too by calling EditableNucleotideGraphSequenceDocument.setSequenceAndAnnotationsAndGraph(CharSequence, java.util.List, NucleotideGraph). Hence, it is illegal to change the length of the sequence through this method if this is instanceof NucleotideGraphSequenceDocument; Therefore, implementations of this method should start with the following code: 
         if (this instanceof NucleotideGraphSequenceDocument && sequence.length() != getSequenceLength()) {
       throw new IllegalArgumentException("Can't change sequence length without updating graph for " + getClass());
 }
        Specified by:
        setSequenceAndAnnotations in interface EditableSequenceDocument
        Overrides:
        setSequenceAndAnnotations in class DefaultSequenceDocument
        Parameters:
        sequence - new residues; NOTE: This CharSequence must not change its length or characters after it was passed to this method!
        annotations - new annotations

        public org.jdom.Element toXML()
        Description copied from interface: XMLSerializable
        Convert object to a JDOM element. The representation should be complete so that XMLSerializable.fromXML(org.jdom.Element) can completely restore the objects representation.

        It is recommended that the returned element use XMLSerializable.ROOT_ELEMENT_NAME as its name, in which case it must not define an attribute called "type". In this case, fromXML, will be called with an element whose name may differ from the element return from this function. This recommendation allows a more compact representation of the XML can be stored.

        This method generally should not be called directly. Instead, you should usually call XMLSerializer.classToXML(String, XMLSerializable) which calls this method internally.

        PluginDocument implementations of this method may choose to throw an XMLSerializationException, enclosed in a RuntimeException.

      • fromXML

        public void fromXML(org.jdom.Element root)
             throws XMLSerializationException
        Description copied from interface: XMLSerializable
        Restore the object from the JDOM Element returned by XMLSerializable.toXML().

        This method generally should not be called directly. Instead, you should usually call XMLSerializer.classFromXML(org.jdom.Element) or XMLSerializer.classFromXML(org.jdom.Element, Class) which calls this method internally.

        It is optional to implement this method. Instead of implementing an empty constructor and implementing this method properly, the implementation may instead throw an UnsupportedOperationException and implement a constructor that takes a single Element as a parameter. This allows for cleaner code such as support for final fields in the XMLSerializable class.

        The element parameter should not be modified since it may be reused. If you need a modified version of it, take a copy with Element.clone().

      • toHTML

        public String toHTML()
        Description copied from interface: PluginDocument
        Provide a textual view of document. The contents should be at most 30K-60K characters. One reason is that this text is rendered using JTextPane, which is horrendously slow when handling large text. The more fundamental reason is that large amounts of text are generally not useful for a user. The whole idea of using a tool such as Geneious is to provide specialized viewers which make the large amount of bioinformatics data perceivable and comprehensible to a human user.

        Return an HTML body fragment (i.e. a fragment which sits inside a <body></body> tag). (Header,stylesheet and annotations are automatically added by GENEious code).

        Can optionally return an entire html tag set, as long as the first six characters are <html>

        Specified by:
        toHTML in interface PluginDocument
        Overrides:
        toHTML in class DefaultSequenceDocument
        Returns:
        an HTML fragment of tag set, or null to have no text view.

      • getBindingInterval

        public SequenceAnnotationInterval getBindingInterval()
        Get the interval for the binding region of the oligo sequence (excluding any 5' extension). This is determined by the interval of the primer_bind or probe_bind annotation on the sequence. If there is no bind annotation then the whole sequence is considered binding and an interval representing the length of the sequence is returned

        The binding region excludes any additional extensions that have been added after the creation of the primer.
        Returns:
        The interval of the binding region in this OligoSequenceDocument. Never null.

      • getExtensionInterval

        public SequenceAnnotationInterval getExtensionInterval()
        Get the interval for the 5' extension region of the oligo sequence . This is the region of the sequence not covered by the primer_bind or probe_bind annotation on the sequence. If there is no bind annotation then there is considered to be no extension.
        Returns:
        The interval of the 5' extension region in this OligoSequenceDocument. Zero-length interval at the start of the binding interval, if there is no extension
        Since:
        API 4.700 (Geneious 7.0.0)

      • getExtensionSequence

        public CharSequence getExtensionSequence()
        Get the sequence of bases making up the 5' extension region of this oligo. This is the region not covered by the primer_bind or probe_bind annotation on the sequence. If there is no bind annotation then there is considered to be no extension.
        Returns:
        The 5' extension sequence for this oligo.
        Since:
        API 4.700 (Geneious 7.0.0)

      • getBindingSequence

        public CharSequence getBindingSequence()
        Get the sequence of bases making up the binding region of this oligo. This is determined by the primer_bind or probe_bind annotation on the sequence. If there is no bind annotation then the whole sequence is considered binding the entire sequence is returned from this method.

        The binding sequence excludes any additional extensions that have been added after the creation of the primer.
        Returns:
        The binding sequence for this oligo. This is the sequence that will be tested for annealing against a target sequence.
